Cook and drain pasta as directed on package. Meanwhile, cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat until crisp, stirring occasionally. Add mushrooms and cook 2 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Stir in wine and cook, stirring constantly, until wine evaporates. Remove bacon and mushrooms from pan and reserve. Cook beef in same skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown; drain. Stir in reserved bacon mixture, cream and pasta sauce. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until hot. Top hot cooked pasta with sauce. Add a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese, if you like.